# Form not submitting

## User issue
The user cannot submit the form.

## Possible causes
- Missing required fields
- Validation error (client-side or server-side)
- The backend endpoint is not responding
- JavaScript issue in form handling
- Network error during submission

## Troubleshooting steps
1. Ask the user to make sure all the required fields are filled out.
2. Ask the user to clear their cache or try a different browser.
3. Ask the user to share any error messages.
4. Test form submission.
5. Check validation rules and backend responses.
6. Check frontend behaviour and API responses.

## User-friendly response
Please make sure all the required fields are filled correctly. 

You can also try clearing your browser cache or trying a different browser.

If the issue occurs, please share any error messages with us so we can identify the problem faster.

## Internal note
The issue may be related to validation errors, JavaScript issues, backend endpoint problems, or API failures. 
